  "Monument": "Patkuli viewing platform",
  "Short": "The Patkuli viewing platform, located in the historic district of Tallinn, offers a picturesque and captivating view of the Old Town, its towers, and walls, extending all the way to the port. Built-in 1903, the stairway leading to the platform consists of 157 steps, connecting Toompea Hill to the lower town. The stairway emerges near Snelli Pond in Toompark, providing a convenient access point.",
  "Medium": "The Patkuli viewing platform, nestled in one of Tallinn's oldest neighborhoods, provides visitors with a serene and mesmerizing view of the Old Town. From this vantage point, one can marvel at the charming medieval architecture, the majestic towers, and the well-preserved city walls. The platform is reached by ascending the scenic stairway constructed in 1903, consisting of 157 steps that connect Toompea Hill to the lower town. The journey down the stairway leads to Toompark, where visitors can further explore the surroundings and enjoy the tranquil atmosphere near Snelli Pond. The Patkuli viewing platform offers a captivating experience, immersing visitors in the rich history and picturesque landscapes of Tallinn.",
