nes from the life of Christ. Epitaphs and coat-of-arms epitaphs were installed on the walls to commemorate notable individuals buried within the church. In subsequent centuries, memorial chapels dedicated to prominent figures were erected, including those of Bogislaus von Rosen, Gustav Adolf Clodt, and Peter August von Holstein-Beck. The Chapel of St. George eventually underwent transformation into the North Hall, serving as a versatile space within the church. Today, St. Nicholas' Church stands as a remarkable testament to Tallinn's rich architectural and artistic heritage. Its grandeur, historical significance, and impressive collection of artworks continue to attract visitors from around the world, allowing them to experience the vibrant history and cultural legacy of this iconic medieval church.",
