  "Monument": "Piiskopi viewing platform",
  "Short": "The Piiskopi observation platform, situated on the western side of Toompea, provides a picturesque view of the Pelgulinna and Kalamaja districts. Also known as the Bishop's Garden, this charming square offers a hidden retreat. During the renovation, the medieval well was restored, and the garden was adorned with paradise apple trees. Additionally, visitors can marvel at the presence of the two oldest oak trees in Toompea.",
  "Medium": "Nestled on the western side of Toompea, the Piiskopi observation platform, affectionately referred to as the Bishop's Garden, beckons visitors with its quaint and serene ambiance. This small, garden-shaped platform offers a captivating view of the Pelgulinna and Kalamaja districts, showcasing the charm of Tallinn's urban landscape. With roots dating back to the 18th and 19th centuries, the Bishop's Garden was once home to the gardens belonging to the nearby Cathedral. During a recent renovation, the garden was lovingly restored, complete with a rejuvenated medieval well and the planting of paradise apple trees, infusing the space with natural beauty and tranquility. Furthermore, the Piiskopi observation platform is graced by the presence of the two oldest oak trees in Toompea, standing as living testaments to the area's rich history and enduring allure.",
  "Long": "Tucked away on the western side of Toompea, the Piiskopi observation platform, colloquially known as the Bishop's Garden, presents visitors with a hidden gem and a breathtaking vista. This intimate square, reminiscent of a charming garden, invites contemplation and offers an enchanting view of the Pelgulinna and Kalamaja districts, showcasing the diverse tapestry of Tallinn's urban landscape. Steeped in history, the Bishop's Garden traces its origins to the 18th and 19th centuries when it served as the grounds for the gardens affiliated with the neighboring Cathedral. During a recent renovation, the garden was meticulously revitalized, paying homage to its historical significance. The restoration efforts included the resurrection of a medieval well, adding a touch of nostalgia and authenticity to the space. The garden was also adorned with the planting of paradise apple trees, infusing the surroundings with vibrant colors and fragrant blooms. Within the Piiskopi observation platform, visitors are captivated by the presence of two ancient oak trees, standing tall as silent witnesses to the passage of time and the enduring spirit of Toompea. These majestic oaks serve as living relics, embodying the rich heritage and natural splendor of the area. As visitors stroll through the Bishop's Garden, they are enveloped by an atmosphere of tranquility and serenity. The view from the Piiskopi observation platform offers a captivating panorama, inviting moments of reflection and appreciation for Tallinn's architectural beauty and urban charm. Whether admiring the distant rooftops or simply savoring the peaceful ambiance, the Bishop's Garden and its observation platform offer a cherished retreat, allowing visitors to connect with the city's past while immersing themselves in the present beauty of the surrounding districts.",
