  "Monument": "Kohtuotsa viewing platform",
  "Short": "The Kohtuotsa viewing platform, located on the northern side of Toompea hill, offers breathtaking vistas of Tallinn's Old Town with its iconic red roofs and majestic spires. From this vantage point, visitors can also marvel at the modern high-rise buildings in the new part of the city, creating a striking contrast. In the distance, the Gulf of Finland, the bustling port, and the picturesque Pirita district complete the panoramic view. Please note that the platform is currently closed for renovation and is scheduled to reopen in October 2022.",
  "Medium": "Perched on the northern side of Toompea hill, the Kohtuotsa viewing platform is a coveted destination for visitors seeking awe-inspiring views of Tallinn's captivating landscapes. From this elevated spot, one can gaze upon the timeless charm of the Old Town, where the sea of red roofs and soaring spires tell stories of centuries past. The juxtaposition of the ancient and the contemporary becomes evident as the view expands to encompass the gleaming high-rise buildings in the new part of the city, symbolizing Tallinn's modern identity. As the eye travels further, the sweeping panorama reveals the enchanting sight of the Gulf of Finland, its waters stretching toward the horizon. The bustling port and the picturesque Pirita district add depth and character to the scenic tapestry. Regardless of the season or weather conditions, the Kohtuotsa viewing platform guarantees unforgettable views that leave a lasting impression. Please note that the viewing platform is temporarily closed for renovation works, aiming to enhance the visitor experience. The anticipated reopening is scheduled for October 2022, when visitors can once again indulge in the mesmerizing vistas that have made this spot a cherished destination.",
  "Long": "Nestled on the northern side of Toompea hill, the Kohtuotsa viewing platform stands as a testament to Tallinn's architectural splendor and natural beauty. From this elevated oasis, visitors are treated to an unrivaled panorama that encapsulates the essence of the city. As one approaches the platform, anticipation builds, knowing that an extraordinary visual feast awaits. Stepping onto the platform, a breathtaking tableau unfolds before the eyes‚Äîa symphony of red roofs and soaring spires, emblematic of Tallinn's Old Town. The meticulously preserved medieval structures seem to whisper tales of bygone eras, transporting visitors to a time of knights and cobblestone streets. But the view doesn't stop there. The Kohtuotsa platform offers a remarkable contrast as it unveils the modern facet of Tallinn. Amidst the historical charm, the city's contemporary identity emerges, embodied by the gleaming high-rise buildings that punctuate the skyline. This juxtaposition of the old and the new paints a vibrant portrait of Tallinn's evolution and resilience. Casting one's gaze further, the horizon expands to reveal the vast expanse of the Gulf of Finland, shimmering under the sun's gentle caress. The bustling port, a gateway to the world, breathes life into the scene, while the serene Pirita district beckons with its natural serenity. The harmonious convergence of land and sea creates a sense of tranquility and connection to nature. It is important to note that the Kohtuotsa viewing platform is currently closed for renovation works, as dedicated efforts are made to elevate the visitor experience. The anticipated reopening is scheduled for October 2022 when visitors can once again immerse themselves in the awe-inspiring beauty that has made this spot an icon of Tallinn.",
