  "Monument": "Funicular Restaurant Complex",
  "Short": "Embark on a journey to the Funicular Restaurant Complex, situated at the peak of the Mtatsminda mountain in Tbilisi. Located within Mtatsminda Park, this culinary gem stands 800 meters above the city, boasting an unsurpassed view of Tbilisi. The complex, dating back to 1905, is undoubtedly one of the city's most significant places. Here, you can savor a blend of delicious food and drink in the most stylish setting, all while enjoying a panoramic view that French botanist Emil Levie likened to the sight of Paris from the top of the Eiffel Tower. Come experience the magic yourself!",
  "Medium": "Nestled at the top of Mtatsminda mountain, which towers 800 meters above Tbilisi, is the Funicular Restaurant Complex. Part of the larger Mtatsminda Park, this upscale dining hub is not only a feast for the palate but also for the eyes, thanks to its unparalleled panoramic view of the city.  Historically, the Funicular Restaurant Complex is among the most significant places in Tbilisi. Its roots stretch back to 1905, marking it as a venerable part of the city's rich cultural fabric. As you dine in the stylishly designed complex, you're taking part in a long-standing tradition of Tbilisians seeking entertainment and refreshment in the beautiful surroundings of Mtatsminda Park.  The complex can be accessed via the historic Tbilisi Funicular, a cable-operated railroad with upper and lower stations that adds a sense of adventure to your culinary journey. As French botanist Emil Levie once wrote after experiencing the view, In the evenings, the city is a wonderful sight from the top. I feel as if I am looking at Paris from the top of the Eiffel Tower. We invite you to come and create your own lasting memories in this timeless venue.",
  "Long": "Welcome to the Funicular Restaurant Complex, a culinary delight nestled high above the hustle and bustle of Tbilisi. Perched atop the 800-meter-high Mtatsminda mountain, this elegant dining hub offers more than just exquisite cuisine; it provides a captivating bird's-eye view of Georgia's capital city that leaves visitors spellbound.  The complex is part of the expansive Mtatsminda Park, which spans more than one square kilometer and has been a cherished leisure spot for generations. This combination of recreation and dining has cemented the park's and the restaurant's reputation as must-visit attractions in Tbilisi.  Historically, the Funicular Restaurant Complex holds immense significance. Its establishment dates back to 1905, making it an integral part of Tbilisi's rich cultural heritage. Every aspect of this dining hub, from its refined architecture to its diverse culinary offerings, narrates a story of the city's evolution and refinement in gastronomy.  Accessibility to the complex is an adventure in itself. The journey begins at the base of the mountain with the Tbilisi Funicular, a historical cable-operated railroad connecting the lower city to the upper heights of Mtatsminda. As the funicular ascends, the cityscape unfolds below, offering a truly mesmerizing sight, preparing you for the grandeur that awaits at the top.  Inside the Funicular Restaurant Complex, you will find an elegant blend of tradition and modernity. The tastefully designed interiors pay homage to Georgian architecture, while also embodying a modern aesthetic that appeals to contemporary tastes. As you sit down to dine, you're not just having a meal but participating in a time-honored tradition of Tbilisians, further enriched by the stunning cityscape that stretches out beneath you.  French botanist Emil Levie once noted, In the evenings, the city is a wonderful sight from the top. I feel as if I am looking at Paris from the top of the Eiffel Tower. It's hard not to share his sentiment as you look out over the twinkling lights of Tbilisi from the complex.  In its long history, the Funicular Restaurant Complex has borne witness to numerous significant events and evolved with the city it overlooks. Today, it stands as an icon of Tbilisi, embodying the city's vibrant culinary scene, rich history, and timeless charm. A visit to the complex offers more than just a dining experience; it's a voyage into the heart of Tbilisi's heritage, promising cherished memories and a true taste of Georgian hospitality.",
