  "Monument": "Fabrika Tbilisi",
  "Short": "Welcome to Fabrika, Tbilisi‚Äôs hotspot for creatives, where an abandoned Soviet-era sewing factory transformed into a buzzing cultural center. Home to artists, innovative businesses, cafes, and the region's largest hostel, Fabrika is a beacon of revitalization and creativity. Its bare walls and raw surfaces echo its industrial past, with the vibrant street art adorning the facade, and a welcoming courtyard stands as a trendy social hub. This architectural marvel is situated in a historic district that, thanks to Fabrika, is now a popular artistic and hipster haven. You can co-create, learn, socialize, or even have a sleepover here. Amidst the exciting hustle and bustle of Fabrika, you'll experience a unique blend of authenticity, innovation, and cultural diversity. ",
  "Medium": "Discover Fabrika, a symbol of Tbilisi's urban transformation. An erstwhile Soviet sewing factory, it's now a bustling cultural hub for artists, local businesses, and tourists alike. Filled with artist studios, shops, educational institutions, urban style cafes and bars, a co-working space, and the region's largest hostel, it's a melting pot of creativity and innovation.  The architects, MUA and Adjara Group Hospitality, respected the building's history while creating an alternative space. With a nod to its industrial past, the aesthetic is purposefully unfinished with bare walls, untouched ceilings and floors. Old appliances found on site have been ingeniously incorporated into the design. The intact facade serves as a canvas for striking street art. The building blocks enclose a welcoming rectangular courtyard, a popular gathering spot that effortlessly blends with the urban context.  Located in a previously overlooked district, Fabrika's inception sparked a neighborhood renaissance. The area, once a quiet corner of the city, is now a vibrant artistic district, teeming with locals and tourists seeking new experiences.  At Fabrika, you'll find yourself immersed in a rich tapestry of cultural diversity. Visitors can engage in cross-exchange of ideas, contribute to projects, or simply soak up the unique atmosphere. From the hostel rooms that echo the industrial past to the lobby filled with comfortable furniture, traditional rugs, and large plants, every corner of Fabrika tells a story.",
  "Long": "Welcome to Fabrika, a cultural epicenter in the heart of Tbilisi, Georgia. What once was an abandoned Soviet-era sewing factory is now a vibrant hub of creativity, a testament to the city's ingenuity and resilience. Here, artists, creators, local businesses, and visitors from around the world come together in a unique synthesis of ideas, art, and culture.  Transformed by MUA (Multiverse Architecture) and Adjara Group Hospitality, Fabrika retains its industrial roots while offering a contemporary, alternative space. With intentional minimalism, the bare walls, untouched floors and ceilings serve as a tribute to its past, while old appliances are imaginatively repurposed as design elements. The exterior facade, largely intact, has been turned into a canvas for dynamic street art.  Within Fabrika's walls, you'll find a thriving community. It hosts artist studios, shops, educational institutions, a co-working space, and the biggest hostel in the region. Whether you're here to co-work, learn, socialize, or sleep, Fabrika caters to every creative need. Offering up to 400 beds, and choices ranging from shared dormitories to apartment-style suites, Fabrika's hostel is a welcoming space that mirrors the industrial aesthetic of the whole complex.  Fabrika is nestled in a historic yet previously underappreciated district of Tbilisi. However, the establishment of Fabrika has breathed new life into the area, converting it into an artistic hotspot frequented by both locals and travelers. The area's popularity has increased manifold, positively influencing its economic and social life.  The design extends beyond aesthetic appeal and offers functional utility. The architecture was meticulously planned to enable accessibility for the disabled and also incorporates energy-efficient systems. The three distinctive building blocks that make up Fabrika surround a rectangular courtyard, a trendy gathering spot that has quickly become the heart of socializing in Tbilisi.  An integral part of the experience at Fabrika is its focus on communal connection. Evenings in the open courtyard buzz with energy, packed with people of different tastes, styles, ages, and social statuses, all sharing their ideas and experiences. This sense of community extends to Fabrika's 22 resident entities - cafes, bars, artist studios, and shops, all contributing to its rich and diverse artistic soul.  At Fabrika, you're not just visiting a building; you're stepping into a living, breathing entity that champions openness, innovation, change, and growth. Here, every visit is an invitation to immerse yourself in a vibrant culture, challenge your perspectives, and become part of Tbilisi's exciting journey of urban transformation. It's more than just a place; it's an experience, a story of revitalization, recreation, and reinvention that continues to shape the face of Tbilisi.",
  "Image": "https://www.wagnerproducciones.com/travelmeit/monumentos_tbilisi/Fabrika%20Tbilisi.jpg"
 },
