  "Monument": "Lisi Lake",
  "Short": "Welcome to Lisi Lake, an oasis of serenity just outside Tbilisi, Georgia. This small lake in the Kura River Valley, known for its rocky terrain and diverse ecosystem, is home to exotic birds, turtles, foxes, and even a large population of snakes. An intriguing feature of Lisi Lake is the Green Lisi Town project, a mixed-use development designed by Andropogon, brought to life by TBC Bank Chairman Mamuka Khazaradze. Enjoy the Mediterranean climate as you stroll around the lake, but remember, the controversial history of its redevelopment continues to stir debates.",
  "Medium": "Uncover the charm of Lisi Lake, a gem nestled in the Kura River valley near Tbilisi, Georgia. This unique spot boasts of a rocky, arid landscape with steppe plots, providing habitats for a diverse range of species including exotic birds, turtles, foxes, hares, and a large population of snakes. The lake is part of the ongoing Green Lisi Town project, a grand development headed by TBC Bank Chairman Mamuka Khazaradze, which, however, has been the center of some controversy. Back in 2007, Khazaradze's group controversially purchased the land under terms that sidestepped original requirements to enhance local ecology. Soak in the warm Mediterranean climate, with mild winters and hot summers, perfect for outdoor adventures. But keep in mind, this scenic escape is not just a natural wonder, but a reflection of Georgian economic and political dynamics.",
  "Long": "Immerse yourself in the tranquil surroundings of Lisi Lake, a picturesque locale in the vicinity of Tbilisi, Georgia. Situated within the Kura River valley, this modest yet captivating lake is set amidst a rocky, arid landscape adorned with shrubs and steppe vegetation. The lake provides a sanctuary for a wide range of fauna - from exotic birds to turtles, foxes, hares, and even a significant population of snakes nestled in the nearby hillsides.  But Lisi Lake isn't just about nature; it also echoes the echoes of ambitious development projects and controversies. The lake's surroundings are home to the Green Lisi Town, a mixed-use development project initiated by TBC Bank Chairman Mamuka Khazaradze. However, the history of its development is steeped in controversy. In 2007, Khazaradze's group purchased the land directly from the city, bypassing a higher original bid and circumventing initial obligations to improve local ecology, stirring considerable debate.  As you wander around Lisi Lake, enjoy the warm Mediterranean climate that characterizes this region. The climate presents mild winters and hot summers, and an occasional rainfall, making it a perfect destination for outdoor adventures all year round. But remember to carry enough water and sun protection during summer, as temperatures can reach up to 37 degrees celsius.  Interestingly, Lisi Lake shares its uniqueness with the enchanting Ritsa Lake in Gagra, located in the temporarily Russian-occupied territory. Known for its changing colors according to the seasons and the surrounding mountain beauty, it's another marvel that complements Georgia's aquatic allure.  Explore Lisi Lake not just as a natural retreat but as a nexus of ecology, development, and controversy, offering insights into Georgia's socio-economic narrative. While the beauty captivates you, the stories will leave you contemplating.",
  "Image": "https://www.wagnerproducciones.com/travelmeit/monumentos_tbilisi/Lisi%20Lake.jpg"
 },
